        <documentation>Entoli Coordination&#xD;
&#xD;
Why it exists:&#xD;
To ensure that every execution is complete, valid, and reproducible before it is performed.&#xD;
&#xD;
What it does:&#xD;
&#xD;
resolves the contract for an intent&#xD;
retrieves rule bindings&#xD;
retrieves canonical rules&#xD;
assembles all required sources&#xD;
produces a fully specified execution package&#xD;
&#xD;
What it does NOT do:&#xD;
&#xD;
no process control&#xD;
no state management&#xD;
no branching logic&#xD;
no interpretation of rules&#xD;
no execution</documentation>
      </element>
